configSetPrices.disclaimer:
Calculator

The information presented on this website is based on data available at the time. Design, specifications, price, and production dates are subject to change without notice and pertain specifically to Hong Kong vehicles. Some features and options may be unavailable when your vehicle enters production.

Financing

Finance offer from ORIX's and is subject to approval at ORIX’s discretion and the terms and conditions of the financing contract. ORIX is solely responsible for the financing arrangements and Tesla does not act on behalf of ORIX nor is registered or licensed to provide financial services or advice.

Wheels

There are different advantages to the 21-inch and 19-inch wheels. For example, the 21-inch wheels generally provide increased handling whereas the 19-inch wheels wear less quickly and provide more protection from obstacles and poor road conditions.
configSetPrices.resale_value_guarantee_text:
Tesla guarantees the resale value of your Model S. After three years, you can trade in your Model S for 70% of the original base price plus 60% of options. Learn more.

Value Loan Program

Tesla Value Loan Program allows customers to pay lower monthly installments. Learn more.

PA01.name: No Paint Armor
PA01.description:
Protect key areas of Model S against stone chips, bug damage, weathering and other paint damage. Paint Armor is clear film that is applied to:
  • Exterior mirrors
  • Front bumper, fascia and hood (nose)
  • Front and rear fender (trailing edge)
  • Front and rear rocker panels
  • Rear bumper fascia

Depending on the angle of sunlight, seams between protected and unprotected paint areas will be visible, particularly on white and pearl white cars.

PX01.name: Performance Plus
PX01.description: Performance Plus adds world class handling to the incredible acceleration of Model S Performance, while also improving range. After hundreds of iterations affecting every detail of the suspension, our vehicle dynamics team was able to achieve the rare outcome of improving both performance and efficiency. In addition to upgraded dampers, bushings, stabilizer bars and tires, the rear tires are 20 mm wider and staggered for improved acceleration on low grip surfaces. C_CHG_SUPER.name: Charging
C_CHG_SUPER.description:
Model S comes standard with an onboard charger and a 40 amp single phase wall connector. For charging on the go, Model S comes standard with IEC 62196 Type 2 — Type 2 standard connector. Charge rates up to 55 kilometers of range per hour of charge are possible depending on the power source.

An optional mobile connector compatible with UK electrical outlets is available through your local service center. The mobile connector is not recommended as a primary charging solution due to variations in the quality and reliability of UK type 1363 outlets. For the best charging experience, please use the Tesla wall connector that comes standard with your Model S.

configSetPrices.gas_disclaimer:
Electric Vehicle IncentivesElectric vehicles are exempt from First Registration Tax. Electric vehicles also benefit from $553 per month in license fee savings.Gasoline Savings

Electric vehicles are less expensive to fuel than gasoline powered vehicles. The average person drives approximately 10,000 km and spends around $13,800 on gasoline per year. In comparison, the cost of electricity to power Model S over the same distance is ten times lower. Over the five year average length of car ownership, that’s approximately $60,000 in gasoline savings.

We've assumed a fuel economy of 8.2 liters per 100 km for a comparable gasoline powered car. We’ve also assumed the regional average of $1.46 per kilowatt hour for electricity, 30% charging on Tesla’s Supercharger network enabling free long distance travel and $16.93 per liter for premium gasoline over the next five years.
